{"name": "bw-save-game", "metadata": {"name": "bw-save-game", "version": "0.0.1", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 4 - Beta", "Programming Language :: Python"], "home_page": "https://github.com/timniederhausen/bw_save_game", "license": "GPL-3.0-only", "documentation_url": "https://pyscaffold.org/", "dependencies": [], "summary": "Editor for Dragon Age: The Veilguard saves.", "upload_time": 1732500911}, "documentation": ["# bw_save_game: BioWare save game tools\r\n\r\n    Edit save games for Dragon Age: The Veilguard\r\n\r\nThis pure-Python library and its console applications (`csav2json`, `json2csav`) can read and write Dragon Age: The Veilguard save files (`*.csav`).\r\nSupport for previous Dragon Age games might follow.\r\n\r\n## Installation\r\n\r\nMake sure you have these programs installed:\r\n\r\n* Python 3.8 or newer\r\n\r\nThis package is available for download from [PyPI][1]. You can install this\r\npackage using `pip`:\r\n```bash\r\npip install --upgrade bw_save_game\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Usage\r\n\r\nFor non-programmers this project ships two applications that can convert a save game into a readable JSON document and vice-versa.\r\nEditing this document allows you to change every part of a save, however, ensuring correctness and consistency is up to you.\r\n\r\n## Contributing\r\n\r\n### Making Changes & Contributing\r\n\r\nThis project uses [pre-commit][4], please make sure to install it before making any\r\nchanges::\r\n\r\n    pip install pre-commit\r\n    cd bw_save_game\r\n    pre-commit install\r\n\r\nIt is a good idea to update the hooks to the latest version::\r\n\r\n    pre-commit autoupdate\r\n\r\nDon't forget to tell your contributors to also install and use pre-commit.\r\n\r\n## Licensing\r\n\r\n[![GNU GPLv3 Image](https://www.gnu.org/graphics/gplv3-127x51.png)][2]\r\n\r\n`bw_save_game` is Free Software: You can use, study, share and improve it at your\r\nwill. Specifically you can redistribute and/or modify it under the terms of the\r\n[GNU General Public License][3] as published by the Free Software Foundation,\r\neither version 3 of the License, or (at your option) any later version.\r\n\r\n[1]: https://pypi.org/project/bw_save_game/\r\n[2]: http://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.en.html\r\n[3]: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl.html\r\n[4]: https://pre-commit.com/\r\n"], "modules": [{"name": "bw_save_game", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [{"name": "bw_save_game.dist_name", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bw_save_game.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bw_save_game.__version__", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "bw_save_game.dumps", "xref": {"fqname": "bw_save_game.db_object_codec.dumps", "project": null}}, {"name": "bw_save_game.loads", "xref": {"fqname": "bw_save_game.db_object_codec.loads", "project": null}}, {"name": "bw_save_game.read_save_from_reader", "xref": {"fqname": "bw_save_game.container.read_save_from_reader", "project": null}}, {"name": "bw_save_game.write_save_to_writer", "xref": {"fqname": "bw_save_game.container.write_save_to_writer", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "bw_save_game.db_object", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "bw_save_game.db_object.from_raw_dict", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "bw_save_game.db_object.to_raw_dict", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "obj", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "bw_save_game.db_object.DbObjectId", "bases": [], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "bw_save_game.db_object.DbObjectId.value", "type": {"name": "bytes", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bytes", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["12 bytes"]}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["We need some type-safe way of representing the different DbO